   "source": [
    "# Map URB: 1 remains 1 (Urban), 2 becomes 0 (Rural)\n",
    "fies_subset_df['URB'] = fies_subset_df['URB'].replace(2, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify the changes\n",
    "print(\"Target Variable Distribution (1 = Urban, 0 = Rural):\")\n",
    "print(fies_subset_df['URB'].value_counts())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bd18213e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Train-Validation-Test Split\n",
    "According to the project specifications, we must ensure proper training-validation-test splits to avoid data leakage. \n",
    "* **Training Set (70%):** Used to train our classical models and neural network.\n",
    "* **Validation Set (15%):** Used to tune hyperparameters and evaluate the models during training.\n",
    "* **Test Set (15%):** Used for the final, unbiased evaluation of our models.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will use the `stratify` parameter to ensure the proportion of Urban and Rural households remains perfectly balanced across all three splits."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
